item.title: [Request] Zoomed Out RS Pictures
item.dc:creator: @PaulT PaulT
item.description:
@PaulT wrote:

Can anyone explain how private servers came about? I never even thought this sort of thing would happen.

Winterlove made Blakescape, and made a thread “A flight over Runescape” I think it was called. He showed people pictures of him spawning lots of party hats and flying and spawning “Nub Clones” etc… And everyone was pretty excited. Then he released the first server source to the private community. RichyT made the first (and for a longtime, the only) good server, which featured sex and um, other features. Anyway, the server spread virally once it was released publically, to all RS communities. Pictures and copies of the sourcecode were everywhere. After a while it calmed down, Jagex made a public statement that was much like all there other public statements “It doesn’t exist. If it does, don’t use it. If you use the thing that doesn’t exist we will ban your character.”.

Read full topic

Good to see you too, Mopar. Congrats with the popularity of the site.

kuiren:

haha disinterested look http://web.archive.org/web/20050313155331/www.kaitnieks.com/scr/showthread.php?t=649

Yeah, I converted all of SCAR 1’s functions into a Visual Basic 6 class and made some decent programs. I think my best one could start at Falador bank, mine a load of iron at the southwest mine, smelt it, and then bank it. I never could get a handle of random events cleanly and eventually gave up any ideas to release my programs publicly. I played with the idea of making a SCAR script to Visual Basic 6 program converter but it just didn’t work out.

But since my friends have begun playing again I’m going to give some of my old ideas another shot.[br][size=1]Posted at: September 08, 2006, 09:18:45 AM[/size][hr]Thanks for the pictures, too.
